{
  "stem": "15082.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we were liberated in Palikrowy, in that village.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "With me was my mom, and dad, and my grandfather, and Junap Olaska, the cousin that we brought up the last few months to hide out with us.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a cold winter.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That March, it's still pretty cold up in that part.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that Thursday that we were liberated, it was just a day of walking around, like in a daze, and not realizing what happened.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And Friday morning, my dad, and I, and Junap, decided to go to Podkamien, which was about five kilometers away, and see what's doing there, if there were any Jews, or you know, whatever's left, and to see.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In spite of-- my mom was worried, because, you know, the uncertainty of what could happen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Yet, we went.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We came into town.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The town was also liberated already.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There was a lot of Russian army in there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "A few Jews were wandering around from my town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We found-- one was a family, [NON-ENGLISH], a mother and two children which have survived, much older than I am, the son.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The-- [NON-ENGLISH] is probably about five or six years older than I am.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they lived right next door to us-- I mean, next house.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we stayed and rejoiced a little bit, you know, finding a few there alive.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We immediately saw there's no reason to stay in Podkamien.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We returned to Palikrowy, where my mother was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The reason my mom didn't go is because from all these months in the bunker, she couldn't walk on her feet.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It Was very hard for her to walk.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We stayed there on Saturday in Palikrowy.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
